The real problem is that TypeScript can't properly infer the `OPTIONS` type when `FlexibleSchema<OPTIONS>` isn't resolvable without the zod library, so it's probably falling back to `{}` or `unknown`. Since the type errors stem from this unresolvable zod type, I should add explicit type annotations to work around it and verify the logic is sound.

